  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project is a clustered randomized controlled trial of a knowledge translation
      intervention of new ACOG guidelines for the diagnosis of poor progress in labor. The intent
      is to reduce the rate of cesarean section (CS) in first time mothers without increasing
      maternal or neonatal morbidity. The guidelines were developed from data from the Consortium
      for Safe Labor. The unit of randomization will be sites in Alberta that deliver
    </textblock>
